# Technical Decisions

## ML Model Selection (Nov 2024)

**Decision:** Use BiRefNet for all users

**Context:**

- Tested U2Net (2s) vs BiRefNet (14s)
- BiRefNet significantly better at:
  - Removing hands/fingers from shots
  - Cleaner edges
  - Better object detection
- U2Net left artifacts and hands in cutouts

**Trade-offs:**

- Slower processing (14s vs 2s)
- Mitigated with: Background processing, progress UX, "AI magic" messaging
- Future optimization: GPU will reduce to ~3-5s

**Business rationale:**

- Quality as baseline competitive advantage vs Canva
- Volume-based freemium (not quality tiers)
- Better App Store reviews with consistent quality

**Future considerations:**

- Add GPU processing when revenue supports it (~$200-500/month)
- Consider U2Net for instant preview + BiRefNet for final
- Monitor user feedback on processing time
